I don't know. באותה שעה אמרו be'ota sha'ah amru at that moment

1346
01:01:40,534 --> 01:01:40,534
they said, לא ישתה אדם

1347
01:01:47,420 --> 01:01:44,863
מים ויתן לתלמידו אלא אם כן שפך מהן lo yishte adam mayim

1348
01:01:44,863 --> 01:01:52,440
veyiten letalmeido ela im ken shafach mehen

1349
01:01:52,440 --> 01:01:55,220
don't drink water and give to your student unless you yourself have

1350
01:01:55,220 --> 01:01:57,424
poured out from them and one last line: רב אשי אמר, Rav

1351
01:01:57,424 --> 01:01:59,083
Ashi amar, רב אשי Rav Ashi says, הילכך האי תלמידא, hilkach hai

1352
01:01:59,083 --> 01:02:02,400
talmida, therefore a certain תלמיד, talmid, דשפיך קמי רביה deshaffich kamey rabbeih

1353
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:05,380
that spills out water in front of his master, לית ביה משום

1354
01:02:05,380 --> 01:02:09,060
אפקירותא leit beih mishum apikureita is not considered to be, אפקירותא apikureita

1355
01:02:09,060 --> 01:02:12,520
we say is heresy, but the גמרא in סנהדרין Sanhedrin defines it

1356
01:02:12,520 --> 01:02:16,160
as disrespect for תורה scholars. So that would not be an act

1357
01:02:16,160 --> 01:02:18,940
of disrespect if somebody's spilling water out in front of their רבי

1358
01:02:18,720 --> 01:02:21,520
Rebbe because they're doing it because they're trying to clean the cup,

1359
01:02:21,520 --> 01:02:24,000
not out of an act of disrespect, and therefore it is something

1360
01:02:24,000 --> 01:02:26,400
we don't want him to die of thirst, so something that therefore

1361
01:02:26,400 --> 01:02:27,032
we would allow.
